oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Eisenhower and Nixon campaign signs
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of two men holding Eisenhower and Nixon campaign signs on Elk Avenue. One sign reads "IKE DICK, Peace, Prosperity, Progress", and has an elephant on it. The other sign reads "Where did he come from where did he go". The Nunn-Bush Shoes sign is seen in the background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Political posters; Stores & shops
